Key Match Events: Baltimore Orioles eliminated the Minnesota Twins from playoff contention with a 7-2 win
Cade Povich pitched 5 2/3 scoreless innings for the Orioles
Post-Match Reflections: The Minnesota Twins completed their historic second-half collapse after going 12-25 over their last 37 games
The Twins allowed two division rivals to pass them in the standings and take their postseason spot
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles secured the No. 4 seed with Friday's victory and will have home-field advantage during next week's AL Wild Card Round
The Twins lost four straight series and are 4-10 over their last 14 games
Others: The Twins' bullpen was over-extended in Thursday's 13-inning loss to the Miami Marlins, leading to a lifeless offense in the loss to the Orioles
